div.div: Commented on #14 Update `tqdm/tqdm` Docfork Content to Use Official README.rst Instead of Shallow Docfork Version

Hey there @antonrisch Thanks for the reply! I'm quite curious how you all are building the tool out ( Docfork definitely seems like the cleanest context MCP available currently). Since you're MIT license, why not use a common dependency that supports all the file types out of the box? Examples would be like: Repomix (my favorite + MIT license as well) or Gitingest Repomix even has power mode features like file summary, directory summary, line numbers, output parseable format (including XML, MD, and TXT output formats), as well as code compression and comment removal (for token optimization).
My current AI workflow usually consists of using repomix across all of the docs content pages of a particular tool/project and then serving the output file as a prompt context knowledge file to my AI agent when working on associated logic. Would be awesome to see Repomix integrated into Docfork (or something along those lines)! Happy to pitch in a few PRs if you see this as useful/helpful -- let me know!
